# The Organization

-   Publicly traded retail bank

-   1 million customers

-   10,000 employees

-   200 branches

-   Founded 1905

# Competitive Landscape

Traditional retail bank landscape -- static for decades. Some top-tier
banks and some smaller banks.

Significantly challenged by two main drivers:

-   New government regulations:

    -   3 years ago, the regulator forced the banks to sell their credit
        card companies. Overnight, they became direct competitors.

    -   Open Banking, forced banks to open their customer data to
        fintech companies for competing services.

-   Advances in technology:

    -   New digital payment services offer complete financial services
        -- Previously only available by retail banking.

# Business Objectives

-   Offer apps and services that provide remarkable digital experiences

-   Provide any number of users with immediate responses

-   Low Time-to-Market: Introducing new digital channels and services,
    fast!

# Technical Objectives

-   Scalability -- Support millions of customers

-   Concurrency -- Thousands of concurrent users

-   Latency -- ms-level response time

-   360° unified view of data from a single source

-   Fast dev cycle -- weeks to launch a new application

# Tecnical Challenges

-   Data originates in multiple systems that are challenging to
    integrate

-   Legacy systems were not designed to support the speed, scale and
    volumes expected (COBOL,z/OS)

-   Should be segregated from the apps for security and cost
    considerations

