# Project Description

You are an architect responsible to design NeoBank's digital
Transformation. Current bank infrastructure is a CBS based on COBOL
code, running on z/OS on IBM iSeries Mainframe.

DB2 serves as a database for all transactions. ADABAS is a database with
customer information.

Your design adds new on-premises deployment. You need to define the
hardware and software aspects of it. Additionally, the on-prem design
syncs to a cloud environment. Both on-premises and cloud environments
run new digital services (some can legally run only on-prem, others can
run in the cloud).

The cloud environment features an API GW to serve the bank's new mobile
app and website.

Your team has one year to launch this MVP.

# High Level Requirements

-   Functional Requirements

    -   The new digital services:

        -   Show account information and balance

        -   Perform bank transfer to another account in the same bank or
            another bank

            -   Add new Fraud detection engine. There are two modes
                --real-time for transfer, and an offline which requires
                more data and processing time

            -   When a fraud is detected, a transaction is cancelled,
                and the customer is informed in the application

        -   Show monthly income/expenses report

        -   Open Banking API (Over REST)

        -   AI agent which consults financially based on the customer
            data. E.g. Cutting expenses, making investments, etc. (only
            this service can run on the cloud and not on-prem)

# Non-Functional Requirements

-   99.999% uptime

-   No Data Loss

-   Account information in the app can be out of date up to 24 hours for
    incoming transactions from other banks, or payments not done through
    the app

-   All transactions must be performed using a CBS transaction

-   Support 100K digital users within 1 year

-   1 year for MVP to go live

-   Monitoring metrics for technical and business insights

-   60 experienced developers. Mostly Java and AWS background. 5 COBOL
    developers.

-   Minimize storage and processing budget (present your calculation of
    operational costs\*)

-   Secure access, GDPR compliance (regional server, the right to delete
    all user data)

-   Within 3 years, 1M digital users, all in the same geographic region

# Project Guidelines

You are required to write a full High Level Design document of the
system, based on the provided template. Formulate assumptions,
constraints and write requirements.

Design-Identify components and flows (user/data), persistency.

No need to implement anything, only write the design!

No need for deep dive into the different components (can be in the high
level flow).
